      <section eId="sec_CCP-462">
        <num>CCP 462</num>
        <heading>462. Â Cumulation by single plaintiff against single defendant</heading>
        <subsection eId="CCP-462__subsec_1">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Each of the actions cumulated is within the jurisdiction of the court and is brought in the proper venue; and</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CCP-462__subsec_2">
          <num>(2)</num>
          <content>
            <p>All of the actions cumulated are mutually consistent and employ the same form of procedure.
Except as otherwise provided in Article 3657, inconsistent or mutually exclusive actions may be cumulated in the same judicial demand if pleaded in the alternative.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=112042</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
